{"URTICA":[{"def":"A genus of plants including the common nettles.","pos":""}],"URTICACEOUS":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a natural order (Urticaceæ) of plants, of which the nettle is the type.","pos":""}],"URTICAL":[{"def":"Resembling nettles; -- said of several natural orders allied to urticaceous plants.","pos":""}],"URTICARIA":[{"def":"The nettle rash, a disease characterized by a transient eruption of red pimples and of wheals, accompanied with a burning or stinging sensation and with itching; uredo.","pos":""}],"URTICATE":[{"def":"To sting with, or as with, nettles; to irritate; to annoy.","pos":""}],"URTICATION":[{"def":"The act or process of whipping or stinging with nettles; -- sometimes used in the treatment of paralysis.","pos":""}]}